---
name: ra-requirement-unit
description: Canonical atomic requirement unit template
---

<ra-requirement-unit>

<description>

Atomic and independently testable requirement unit.

</description>

<guidelines>

Use one unit per need, keep implementation-free wording, and set `Approved` only after explicit user approval.

</guidelines>

<template>

```xml
<req id="FR-AREA-0001" type="FR" level="System" ticketId="JIRA-0000" classification="business|technical">
  <title>...</title>
  <statement>...</statement>
  <rationale>...</rationale>
  <source>User|Inferred|Sources|Documentation</source>
  <priority>Must|Should|Could|Wont</priority>
  <status>Draft|Approved|Deprecated</status>
  <approved_by>[user login approved]</approved_by>
  <changed>[YYYY-MM-DD]</changed>
  <verification>Test|Analysis|Inspection|Demo</verification>
  <acceptance>
    <criteria>Given: A When: B Then: C.</criteria>
    <criteria>Given: X When: Y Then: Z.</criteria>
  </acceptance>
  <depends>FR-AREA-0000, NFR-0000, INT-AREA-0000</depends>
  <implementation>[Implemented|Todo|Modify] [Additional Notes: files affected for implemented, notes without duplication for what changed for todo and modify]</implementation>
  <notes>...</notes>
</req>
```

</template>

</ra-requirement-unit>
